    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-05-27T09:16:54+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-27T09:16:54+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-26T23:46:54Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-26T23:46:54Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A low pressure system lies over the north of the state, weakening as it moves into NSW today. A weak ridge of high pressure begins to move across SA mid week. A cold front is expected to move over the west and southeast of SA on Friday. A high pressure system moves into the west on Saturday and then moves into the north on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW009" description="Flinders" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-05-27T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-28T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-26T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-27T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower north of Hawker, most likely in the afternoon and evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending south to southeasterly in the late afternoon then becoming light in the evening. Daytime maximum temperatures between 15 and 19.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 11:10am to 1:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-05-28T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-29T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-27T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-28T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Hawker. Slight chance of a shower near the coast, near zero chance elsewhere. Light winds. Overnight temperatures falling to between 5 and 9 with daytime temperatures reaching around 17.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-05-29T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-30T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-28T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-29T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Slight chance of a shower near the coast, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds west to northwesterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 6 and 9 with daytime temperatures reaching between 16 and 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-05-30T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-31T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-29T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-30T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers south of Hawker, medium chance elsewhere. Winds westerly 15 to 25 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 6 and 9 with daytime temperatures reaching between 15 and 19.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
